As early as mid-July, Gewobag won back 670 apartments in Berlin's Karl-Marx-Allee, the weekly Der Spiegel recalled on its website. The price was not published by the council at the time. The dispute over the apartments on the former exhibition avenue from the GDR times was accompanied by protests and filled the front pages of the German press. It became a symbol of the difficult situation of tenants in large German cities, the paper wrote.
