On 27 September 2019, Prime Minister Andrej Babiš and his wife Monika visited the Ground Zero memorial to the terrorist attacks of 11 September 2001 in New York.
Terrorism is the main enemy against which all countries of the world should fight together. At the end of a five-day visit to the United States, Czech Prime Minister Andrej Babiš said this today at the New York memorial to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. On this occasion, the Prime Minister honored the memory of two victims of Czech origin.
