Annex 12 / Safety rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases shall have the meanings set out below:
Security incident means any breach of confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information Asset means any information, process, hardware or software component that (1) supports the Licensee's business activities, or (2) has value to the Licensee, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorized alteration or unavailability adversely affects the Licensee.
Contractor's persons means persons who are directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the subject of this Agreement, including the persons of the Contractor's subcontractors.
The environment of the Authorized Entity means the premises in which the Authorized Entity carries out its business activities and the information and communication systems that the Authorized Entity uses and that contain Information Assets.
2. Personnel security
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 has no criminal record;
2.1.2 has not previously been convicted of a deliberate crime and is not being prosecuted at the time of the performance of the subject of this Agreement,
2.2 If the Contractor detects any non-compliance with the above-mentioned rules on the part of the Contractor's Persons, the Contractor must immediately inform the Client of this. The Client is entitled to demand that such a person no longer participate in the implementation of work arising from the subject of this Agreement, either directly or indirectly, and is entitled to demand that the Contractor ensure adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Client with a complete list of the names of the Contractor's Persons. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Client in advance about changes in the staffing of the performance of this Agreement.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 they must be familiar with these safety rules,
2.4.2 have all the necessary examinations and attestations that result from the law or the requirements of the regulator for the type of work they are to perform in connection with the performance of this Agreement,
2.4.3 regularly provide training in the field of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Person may not enter the Entity's Environment under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances, or bring weapons, explosives, flammables, means of combat, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances that endanger human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 The access of the Contractor's Persons to the Entity's Environment is permitted only if their presence is necessary for the performance of work obligations arising from this Agreement.
3.2 The Contractor's persons are always accompanied by the Customer's responsible employee in the Authorized Entity Environment.
3.3 The free movement of the Contractor's Persons in the Authorised Entity's Environment is only permitted if the given person has been issued a personal access card. The Contractor's Person may not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties to access the Authorised Entity's Environment.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to inform the Client without delay.
3.5 Without undue delay after completion of the work arising from this Agreement or after termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access of the Contractor's Persons to the Authorized Entity's Environment is no longer necessary, the Client shall ensure that all Contractor's Persons return the borrowed access cards to the Client.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor's Person may not remove any Information Assets from the Entity's Environment via a storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the Contractor's Persons in the Authorized Entity Environment
4.1 The Contractor's employees are only assigned accounts that allow the user to be uniquely identified, and only with the permissions they need to perform their duties under this Agreement.
4.2 The Contractor performs routine work tasks under non-privileged accounts, using accounts with administrator privileges only in necessary cases.
4.3 The Contractor's persons may not access the Internet if they work under an account with administrator privileges or with applications that are run under administrator privileges.
4.4 Inactive accounts of the Contractor's Persons are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Client.
4.5 The Contractor shall only use shared accounts with the prior written consent of the Customer.
4.6 In the event of disclosure of the password or in the event of suspicion of disclosure of the password, the Contractor must immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Dealing with certificates
5.1 Access to certificates (both logical and physical) will only be granted to those Contractor's Persons for whom such access is necessary for the performance of their work duties.
5.2 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not provide or make the certificates available to third parties.
5.3 After their installation, the certificates may only be stored in a secure repository in places where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and all other copies shall be destroyed in a manner that makes it impossible to restore them.
5.4 If possible, the private key of the certificate must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to immediately inform the Client of the loss or suspicion of the loss of confidentiality of the certificate's private key.
6. Handling of Information Assets
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited only to places that exclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is prohibited to work with Information Assets in means of public transport, in public places and in places where there is a risk of observation from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work arising from this Agreement, the Contractor shall, without undue delay, return or remove all Information Assets stored in the Contractor's environment, unless the possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be carried out in a manner that makes it impossible to restore them.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not provide access to the Information Assets to any third parties that are not authorized to participate in the performance of this Agreement.
6.4 The Contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which the Information Assets are stored, processed or through which they are transmitted. In connection with the Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders and/or files to prevent unauthorised access to information assets;
6.4.2 tools for the detection and removal of malicious code are used with the setting of regular updates of the database of signatures of malicious code with a frequency not exceeding one week, and appropriate processes for monitoring, logging and responding to positive findings of malicious code are set up,
6.4.3 processes for updating security patches for software components are defined, set up, executed and monitored at an interval not exceeding one month from the release of the patches,
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall, which is connected to supervision, and the Contractor's Persons, during remote access, use exclusively an encrypted VPN connection, which prevents unauthorized interception and alteration of the transmitted communication.
6.5 If the Information Assets are transferred by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorized Entity, the Contractor is obliged to consistently ensure the physical security of these assets and to keep these Information Assets under constant supervision. The Contractor is obliged to comply with the security and operating instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Working in an Entity Environment
7.1 The Contractor is obliged to become familiar with and act in accordance with the standard for the classification of Information Assets if the Client provides it.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Customer or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Customer, the Contractor may not make changes to the configuration of this hardware not approved by the Customer. In particular, the Contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware installed in this way, the process of applying security patches must be explicitly and formally defined, including the responsibilities arising from the roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not install or run any software not approved in advance by the Customer.
7.4 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor is not entitled to carry out any testing of physical or logical security or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorized Entity.
7.5 The contractor must not manipulate the audit records in any way.
7.6 The Contractor's persons are not authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 The Contractor's persons may not carry out any activities harmful to other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code or participating in attacks aimed at disabling the availability of services.
7.8 The Client logs all actions performed by the Contractor's Persons and keeps a record of them for a period of 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Customer, the Contractor's Persons may not connect their own storage devices to any computer equipment of the Authorized Entity.
7.10 At the provided workplace, the Contractor's Persons are obliged to ensure during the time of physical absence:
7.10.1 cleanliness and tidiness so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to Information Assets so that no unauthorised access to these Information Assets can occur.
7.11 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor's persons are not entitled to install equipment enabling remote monitoring or to make any audio or video recordings.
8. Crisis management
8.1 The Contractor's persons are obliged to prevent, to the greatest extent possible, the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the property of the Beneficiary could occur.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Contractor's Person, who is physically present at the place of the event, is obliged without exception and delay to comply with the regulations and directives in force in the locality and to follow the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercises.
8.3 In the event of crisis management, the Contractor's Person is obliged to immediately follow the instructions of the Customer's crisis manager.
9. Reporting security incidents
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, it is obliged to report it immediately to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (telephone: +420 221 710 911).
