Overview of bank accounts for children on the Czech market
Children's accounts are provided by banks free of charge. However, it is necessary to consider the offer, because some other services for accounts are already charged. "The motivation of banks to offer accounts for children, whose basic management is usually free, is straightforward. Financial institutions expect that the waived fees will be returned to them one day. Given the low migration of Czechs between banks, they are probably right," says Kristýna Kuncová from dTest.
According to her, "small accounts" can do almost everything that accounts for adults can do. The child gets their own payment card, can enter payments, track movements on the account, somewhere they have their own electronic banking. Banks will set up the account, but it is up to the parents to teach the children how to use it and also to check their payments.
"Parents can set fairly flexible weekly or monthly limits, turn individual services on and off, and so on. Above all, however, they can monitor what is happening on the account, whether by browsing the internet or thanks to information SMS. Beware, these may no longer be free," adds Kuncová, adding: "If a parent is considering an account for their child, they should consider their abilities and options."
