The pair wrapped the bitch in tape and drowned her in the river, the children found the bag
The case took place at the end of July in the village around Valašské Klobouk. A 27-year-old woman brought home a one- to two-year-old dog that she wanted to take care of. However, her partner, who is ten years older, did not like the fact that it was a bitch, so he decided to get rid of her.
"He wrapped the animal in duct tape and rope and significantly eliminated its vocal expression. He put the dog in a jute bag, which he tied up. Then they drove the animal together to the river, where they threw it in a bag. At the moment when the dog was thrown into the water, the dog was demonstrably alive," said Zlín police spokeswoman Monika Kozumplíková.
The next day, children playing by the river found a jute bag on the bank, and when they opened it, they discovered the body of a dead dog inside, so they called a woman who was passing by and fled. The woman reported the incident to the 158 police emergency line.
"Thanks to the knowledge of the inhabitants of the town, the police officers found out who was probably the perpetrator of this incredible act. And they were not mistaken. Both the man and the woman confessed to the crime and described how the event took place," the police spokeswoman added.
An expert opinion from the field of veterinary medicine confirmed that the dog died in a clearly agonizing way as a result of suffocation, when the animal suffered for several minutes before dying.
"The actions of the perpetrators undoubtedly indicate a clear intention to get rid of the animal at all costs in this reprehensible way, even though they could have donated or sold the dog. The commissioner of the criminal police from Zlín accused the pair of committing the crime of animal cruelty committed in complicity. Both of the still unpunished charges could spend up to three years behind bars if convicted," noted Kozumplíková.
