The opening of Pumpkin World delayed the ripening of pumpkins
Nová Ves u Leština (Havlíčkobrodsko) - A farm in Nová Ves u Leština in Havlíčkobrodsko has opened Pumpkin World today for more than a month. Decorations made up of thousands of freshly harvested pumpkins are dominated by massive orange pyramids in the garden. The autumn event, which is becoming a tradition, starts a week later this year, because the pumpkins on the surrounding seven hectares of the Pipkova family's fields have matured longer. There are still a lot of them in the field, Jaroslava Pipková told ČTK today.
The Pipkas grow many types of pumpkins, but the weather has not been kind to them in the last two years. This year's harvest was delayed and some types did not work out. "As usual, we have enough orange pumpkins for Halloween, but some types for connoisseurs did not work out," said Pipková. Nevertheless, there are more types to choose from on the farm, from the already mentioned large pumpkins suitable for carving and chiseling decorations through pumpkins for cooking hokaido or elongated "spaghetti" to ornamental gourds of various colors and shapes.
Growing pumpkins is laborious. Farmers manually hoe the plants and harvest their fruits, and cut pumpkins from the stem with scissors. Pipka's Pumpkin World has been open regularly since 2010, and previous years have attracted thousands of people. Pumpkin decorations are complemented by attractions made of straw or a maze of logs. Visitors will also see animals kept on the farm. It will be open daily until 3 November.
Details of the event are on the farm's website, where growers also offer some recipes for pumpkin dishes, such as pumpkin muffins or juice. Visitors themselves tell them about other ways to prepare pumpkin in the kitchen. "A lot of cookbooks have tried their recipes, and we let ourselves be inspired," said Pipková. She noted that some housewives also pickle pumpkins like cucumbers.
