Almost 60 percent of Austrians fear that some Muslims are terrorists, 48 percent would like to see a ban on the construction of mosques, and 80 percent would like to see more monitoring of Islamic centers.
The majority of Austrians also want Muslims to be restricted in their religious practices and say that the presence of Muslims sometimes makes them feel like foreigners in their own country.
