According to estimates by the Austrian Ministry of the Interior, approximately 700,000 Muslims live in Austria, which has a population of approximately 8.7 million. The vast majority have Turkish roots. There are more than 400 Muslim places of worship and mosques in the country, and Islam has been officially recognized as a religion since 1912.
