In his case, the increased motivation is more than understandable. Hradec Králové hockey defender Richard Nedomlel will play in Friday's game against the club where he recently played. However, the former Spartan is convinced that his teammates will be similarly motivated, even though they have never worn the jersey of the Prague club.
"Everyone wants to do well against Sparta," says the Hradec back before the match of the 5th extra-league round.
Hradec Králové will try to extend its winning streak, which currently includes three three-point wins in a row. After Kladno and Pilsen, the most appreciated by fans came on Sunday, Mountfield went to neighboring Pardubice.
"But we can't look at the games as they were. We need to focus on the matches that await us now, and play them in the same way, if not better," the Hradec Králové defender points out.
Hradec should not look back at last year's record with Sparta. They lost three out of four games, taking points only once after winning in Prague after extra time. In addition, the Sparta management brought in several significant reinforcements in the summer and expects the team to return to the top.
"Sparta has always had quality players, but let's face it, this year they are really busy," admits Nedomlel before the first game at the end of this week.
And the second? Also a nice shift, waiting for Mountfield on Sunday afternoon in Třinec.
