Lucie Bílá's father was not a fan of her at all. You won't believe what she had to do for a living!
Who does not know that the national treasure Lucie Bílá (53) is originally a seamstress and her real name is Hana Zaňáková, probably does not live in the Czech Republic. But the singer herself has now revealed that she almost worked in a glass factory!
Lucie Bílá knew from a relatively early age that she wanted to be a singer. Her love for singing was born when, as a little girl, she performed in a cultural house in her native Otvovice, where the warbler still lives.
"And I remember exactly where my mother was sitting. That's when the singer was born in me," she admitted to Impulsu radio.
But her father was a little worried about his daughter's future and advised her to take the path of a craft that has a golden bottom.
"My dad always said: 'Skill girl, skill. Walk with your feet on the ground!' He even tried to persuade me to go to the local glassworks. The glassworks no longer works, but I sort of do. I'm a trained seamstress and at home I make various rosaries and pendants from beads, which I then auction off at auctions and use the money to buy wheelchairs," she added with a laugh.
